### Authentication Endpoints

- `POST /api/auth/jwt/create/` - Obtain JWT token
- `POST /api/auth/jwt/refresh/` - Refresh JWT token
- `POST /api/auth/jwt/verify/` - Verify JWT token
- `POST /api/auth/users/` - Register new user
- `POST /api/auth/users/activation/` - Activate user account
- `GET /api/auth/users/me/` - Get current user profile
- `PUT /api/auth/users/me/` - Update current user profile

## Deployment

### Environment Variables

Before deploying to production, make sure to:

1. Generate a new `DJANGO_SECRET_KEY`:
   ```bash
   python -c 'from django.core.management.utils import get_random_secret_key; print(get_random_secret_key())'
   ```

2. Update all environment variables in `.env` or your hosting platform
3. Set `DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE=config.settings.production`
4. Configure `DJANGO_ALLOWED_HOSTS` with your domain
5. Set up a production database
6. Configure email settings for production
7. Set up Redis for caching

### Static Files

Collect static files before deployment:

```bash
uv run manage.py collectstatic --noinput
```

### Database Migrations

Always run migrations in production:

```bash
uv run manage.py migrate --noinput
```

